HEADWORD: Pentail
<hw>Pen"tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
peculiar insectivore (<spn>Ptilocercus Lowii</spn>) of Borneo; -- so
called from its very long, quill-shaped tail, which is scaly at the base
and plumose at the tip.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

